    <briefdescription>
<para>A <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1spawn_1_1logic_1_1SpawnCondition" kindref="compound">SpawnCondition</ref> that triggers spawning at fixed time intervals. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1spawn_1_1logic_1_1TimerSpawnCondition" kindref="compound">TimerSpawnCondition</ref> uses a countdown timer to determine when GameObjects should be spawned. Each time the countdown reaches zero, it resets and increments the spawn budget. If the elapsed time exceeds multiple intervals (e.g., during a frame spike), multiple objects will be budgeted for spawning.</para>
<para>Example usage: ```cpp // Spawn one object every 2 seconds auto condition = std::make_unique&lt;TimerSpawnCondition&gt;(2.0f);</para>
<para>auto spawnSystem = std::make_unique&lt;GameObjectSpawnSystem&gt;( std::move(pool), level, std::move(condition), std::move(strategy) ); ```</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1spawn_1_1logic_1_1SpawnCondition" kindref="compound">SpawnCondition</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>GameObjectSpawnSystem </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
